I"Š<h2 id="install-latex">Install LaTeX</h2>

<p>Latex is composed of many softwares working together, in order to use them easily it exists what we call distribution : they combine all the needed tools in one big package.</p>

<h3 id="install-latex-windows">Install Latex Windows</h3>

<p>Download and install the windows texlive version(install-tl-windows.exe) <a href="https://tug.org/texlive/acquire-netinstall.html">https://tug.org/texlive/acquire-netinstall.html</a>. This is the distribution we will use during the class.</p>

<p>You can also install the texmaker gui <a href="https://www.xm1math.net/texmaker">https://www.xm1math.net/texmaker</a></p>
<h3 id="install-latex-macos">Install Latex MacOs</h3>

<p>Download and install the mac texlive version (called mactex) <a href="https://www.tug.org/mactex/mactex-download.html">https://www.tug.org/mactex/mactex-download.html</a></p>

<p>You can also install the texmaker gui <a href="https://www.xm1math.net/texmaker">https://www.xm1math.net/texmaker</a></p>

<h3 id="install-latex-linux">Install Latex Linux</h3>

<h4 id="debian--ubuntu">Debian / Ubuntu</h4>

<p>Latex package can be directly installed into the system by running :</p>

<p><code class="language-html highlighter-rouge">sudo apt install texlive-base</code></p>

<p>You can also install the texmaker gui <a href="https://www.xm1math.net/texmaker">https://www.xm1math.net/texmaker</a></p>

<p><code class="language-html highlighter-rouge">sudo apt install texmaker</code></p>

<h4 id="fedora-and-yum-based-distribution">Fedora and yum based distribution</h4>

<p><code class="language-html highlighter-rouge">yum install texlive-scheme-full</code></p>

